1
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:08,730
I didn't get much sleep.

2
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:10,590
Are you okay?

3
00:00:10,590 --> 00:00:13,470
Yeah. Oh, that was scary!

4
00:00:13,470 --> 00:00:14,480
Yeah.

5
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,490
Akari! Where have you been?

6
00:00:17,780 --> 00:00:20,160
We were worried!

7
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:23,000
I was stargazing on the beach and fell asleep.

8
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,440
What the heck?

9
00:00:23,630 --> 00:00:25,930
Watanabe-san's pretty free-spirited, isn't she? Seriously?

10
00:00:25,930 --> 00:00:26,860
Yeah.

11
00:00:31,190 --> 00:00:32,760
Yakuin?

12
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:35,880
Jiro-kun was at the beach, too?

13
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:43,720
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

14
00:00:52,950 --> 00:00:54,830
It's criminal to be so shy

15
00:00:54,830 --> 00:00:58,690
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

16
00:00:59,410 --> 00:01:01,000
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

17
00:01:02,010 --> 00:01:04,280
No less than supreme

18
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:07,690
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

19
00:01:08,580 --> 00:01:10,300
The wild ringing of bells

20
00:01:11,330 --> 00:01:17,410
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

21
00:01:18,170 --> 00:01:21,090
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

22
00:01:23,130 --> 00:01:26,640
A daydream that seems like fiction

23
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:29,680
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

24
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,100
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

25
00:01:32,410 --> 00:01:34,720
My heart hurts and hurts,

26
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:39,610
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

27
00:01:39,610 --> 00:01:43,090
It's TRUE FOOL LOVE! Hold me tight!

28
00:01:43,090 --> 00:01:45,410
Be brave, my darling

29
00:01:45,410 --> 00:01:47,990
It won't all be happy and fun

30
00:01:47,990 --> 00:01:50,010
It's all up to us

31
00:01:50,010 --> 00:01:52,220
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

32
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:55,870
Please look my way, darling

33
00:01:56,890 --> 00:02:04,970
Please notice my pure love for you

34
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,530
For some reason, I couldn't really sleep.

35
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:16,990
Oh! Morning.

36
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:19,740
Morning. Are you on your way to brush your teeth?

37
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,990
Yeah. Are you on your way back?

38
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:26,950
Whoa. The sight of Shiori in her pajamas really hits hard.

39
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:30,290
Tenjin sees this every day, doesn't he? Damn.

40
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:32,750
H-Hey, Jiro-kun...

41
00:02:36,050 --> 00:02:39,760
Nothing! Let's give it our best in the kitchen again today, okay?

42
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,670
Yeah.

43
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:50,770
Hey, if it isn't Jiro! Morning!

44
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:52,900
Yeah... Morning.

45
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,630
What? Did something happen? You seem kinda down.

46
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:58,650
Not really.

47
00:03:01,210 --> 00:03:03,660
Could it be that you can't help remembering...

48
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:06,160
what happened last night?

49
00:03:10,850 --> 00:03:13,610
Hey, come on! That's gross!

50
00:03:21,260 --> 00:03:24,570
That's a secret between husband and wife, okay?

51
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:27,670
Damn it.

52
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,570
She'll be treating me like a pushover for a while.

53
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:35,150
I'm glad she just laughed it off, though.

54
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,940
Things'd still be awkward otherwise.

55
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:41,680
That's her way of being considerate of my feelings, right?

56
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:44,450
I need to get it together, too!

57
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:52,820
Oh, by the way, are you gonna be doing the thing tonight, Shiori?

58
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:54,460
The recreational activity? I am.

59
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:58,120
Talk about cliché, right? I heard it's a test of courage.

60
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:01,830
Wh-What do I do, Jiro-kun?!

61
00:04:01,830 --> 00:04:03,430
I'll never make it through that!

62
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:05,220
Whoa, hang on!

63
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:09,600
I was on a bench at the beach last night...

64
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:13,280
And I heard voices! I just know there's something here at this beach!

65
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,730
You must have imagined it!

66
00:04:14,730 --> 00:04:16,690
I just don't know what to do.

67
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:19,360
I'm going to cause so much trouble for whoever I'm paired with.

68
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:23,300
I-It'd be nice if we were paired up together, wouldn't it?

69
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:26,130
I already know that you scare easily,

70
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:28,100
and it's no trouble for me.

71
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:30,120
You wouldn't need to explain anything.

72
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,700
Yeah. Thanks, Jiro-kun.

73
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:37,250
You know, I really love that kind side you have.

74
00:04:40,210 --> 00:04:40,790
Huh?

75
00:04:45,050 --> 00:04:47,760
Wh-What I... What I meant was...

76
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:51,100
No, I know! It's just that I don't get called kind very often,

77
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,520
so it took me by surprise.

78
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:57,720
Sorry for just blurting that out!

79
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,470
I'll go take the trash out now!

80
00:05:05,350 --> 00:05:09,330
Sh-She said "love." Does that word have other meanings?

81
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:12,540
My kind side...

82
00:05:12,540 --> 00:05:13,790
I wuv it!

83
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,040
You scared me!

84
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:19,840
Why are you the only one having a nice, green springtime, damn it?!

85
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,800
What? How long have you been here?

86
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:25,420
Since you tried to entice her out tonight with that lewd look on your face!

87
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:27,870
That phrasing is misleading! And you should've said something!

88
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:30,330
I read the room and waited so I wouldn't interfere

89
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:32,860
with the springtime of my buddy's youth!

90
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:34,180
Thank you for that.

91
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:36,340
Don't go getting a big head over this, you hear?

92
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,280
It wasn't you that Sakurazaka-san said she loved!

93
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:42,890
It was your personality! Personality

94
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,570
I know that.

95
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:46,870
Do you want...

96
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,120
the power?

97
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:51,950
Huh?

98
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:57,260
You're saying you don't want the power to pair up with Sakurazaka-san?

99
00:05:57,830 --> 00:06:00,100
Who do you think you're dealing with here?

100
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,990
I'm the younger brother of the guy who hired you!

101
00:06:02,990 --> 00:06:04,060
That didn't sound cool!

102
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:08,370
The test of courage is the biggest event of this part-time job.

103
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:11,470
Test of Courage

104
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:11,470
According to my brother, the suspension bridge effect... Suspension Bridge Effect

105
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:15,770
may or may not have taken things in a good direction for pairs in the past.

106
00:06:12,430 --> 00:06:16,980
A Good Direction

107
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:16,980
Which is it?

108
00:06:17,490 --> 00:06:21,650
And every year, those pairings are chosen by lottery.

109
00:06:21,650 --> 00:06:23,890
An act as simple as tampering with that lottery

110
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:26,490
would be child's play for me, the little brother.

111
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:33,740
30 Gem Pulls SSR Guaranteed Sakurazaka ShioRi

112
00:06:28,550 --> 00:06:31,980
For the cost of thirty gem pulls!

113
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,250
Okay, everyone! Come draw lots!

114
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,920
Mine's a heart.

115
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,620
What is this? A bear?

116
00:06:40,910 --> 00:06:43,750
These drawings are so bad! Mine's a yacht.

117
00:06:45,810 --> 00:06:46,880
What's yours, Shiori?

118
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:50,130
A sunflower, but...

119
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,720
Are you still worried?

120
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:55,150
I just feel like I'll cause trouble for whoever I'm with.

121
00:06:55,150 --> 00:07:00,000
It'll be fine. Some of them are dull, but no one here's a bad guy.

122
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,650
They'll take the lead for you.

123
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:03,110
But...

124
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,650
It's going to be fine.

125
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:15,530
Girls Ohashi → Yacht Takamiya → Bear Watanabe → Heart Sakurazaka → Sunflower Hamano → Bunny Shiori said hers is the sunflower.

126
00:07:15,530 --> 00:07:17,460
Thank you so much!

127
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,520
This is perfect!

128
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,600
Hey, can I ask you something?

129
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,540
Yes?

130
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:26,690
You said this was to grant Yakuin and Shiori's wish,

131
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:28,080
but is that really all?

132
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,550
Uh, yeah, that's all. Why?

133
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:35,400
Then couldn't you have marked two of the lots and had them draw those?

134
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,350
Was there really any need to use me?

135
00:07:37,350 --> 00:07:40,270
Oh, well... Jiro-chan is one thing,

136
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:44,320
but I thought Sakurazaka-san might object to a trick like that.

137
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:49,050
And worst case, if Sakurazaka-san didn't draw the marked lot because of that,

138
00:07:49,050 --> 00:07:52,780
I don't think I'd be able to help Jiro through the depression it'd cause.

139
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:57,280
For Sakurazaka-san, at least, I want to make it seem like a coincidence.

140
00:07:58,090 --> 00:07:58,880
You...

141
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:01,790
Yes?! Have I done a bad thing?

142
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:04,730
No. I didn't expect it, but you're a pretty decent guy.

143
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:06,300
Huh? Aw, well...

144
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:08,910
You're doing this for your friend, too, aren't you?

145
00:08:08,910 --> 00:08:10,800
You're doing all you can to help me out!

146
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:14,220
I see. If that's how it looks, then I'm glad.

147
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:18,240
No mistakes, okay? Good luck!

148
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,310
O-Okay!

149
00:08:21,860 --> 00:08:25,440
Seriously, don't call me a good person.

150
00:08:25,850 --> 00:08:30,350
I'm just a jerk who's using your friend.

151
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:34,450
Whew. I thought she'd caught on.

152
00:08:35,130 --> 00:08:39,320
Hey, can you make other pairs besides just me and Shiori?

153
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:39,950
Huh?

154
00:08:40,330 --> 00:08:41,720
For Akari...

155
00:08:42,210 --> 00:08:44,370
Could you pair her up with Tenjin?

156
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:46,480
What? Why, though?

157
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:49,090
Please! I'll pay for double the number of gems.

158
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:51,590
J-Jiro-chan...

159
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,760
She's been stressing out a lot, too.

160
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:58,850
And we've been going through all this saying we'd try our hardest together.

161
00:08:59,730 --> 00:09:02,260
If I'm the only one who gets a chance... it just feels wrong.

162
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,860
I don't want to leave her behind on her own.

163
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,060
Sheesh.

164
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:12,220
When you look at me like that, I can't bring myself to take double the gems.

165
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:14,780
But is this really the right thing to do?

166
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,780
And so!

167
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:20,410
We will proceed with these pairings!

168
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:21,920
Glad to be paired with you.

169
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,660
N-No, the pleasure's all mine.

170
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:25,270
Looking forward to it, Watanabe.

171
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:26,540
Y-Yeah.

172
00:09:26,540 --> 00:09:29,640
Hey, my lottery luck is super bad, huh?

173
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:32,240
Are you trying to pick a fight here, you jerk?

174
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,680
I'll be counting on you, Glasses-kun!

175
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,980
Ow, ow, ow! I'm sorry!

176
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:34,980
Of course!

177
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:37,550
You're gonna break it! You're gonna break it! So I'm just thrown in with the odds and ends, huh?

178
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:40,700
I've left colored cones at four sites.

179
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:43,680
Please head to your respective starting points!

180
00:09:44,030 --> 00:09:47,210
We're over there. Shall we head over, Watanabe?

181
00:09:47,210 --> 00:09:47,940
Yeah.

182
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,940
Come on, Jiro. You two get going, too!

183
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:58,500
I hate this! I wanna go back already!

184
00:09:59,860 --> 00:10:02,700
I never would've guessed you'd scare so easily.

185
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:06,420
Does this help? Or is it better not to hold hands?

186
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:08,930
H-Holding hands is... better.

187
00:10:08,930 --> 00:10:10,740
Let's stay like this, then.

188
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:12,460
Th-Thanks.

189
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:15,460
So this is Minami-kun's hand.

190
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:18,470
Even though they're both guys, it's a little different.

191
00:10:19,330 --> 00:10:21,470
Jiro's hand is more...

192
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:24,150
Wait, Jiro has nothing to do with this!

193
00:10:24,150 --> 00:10:25,720
What is it, Watanabe?

194
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,990
Uh... N-Nothing!

195
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:30,350
Just thinking about something, kinda.

196
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:34,770
Oh, right! The chat! Let's see how the other teams are doing!

197
00:10:34,770 --> 00:10:35,640
Huh?

198
00:10:37,430 --> 00:10:40,250
I think... I might've dropped my smartphone.

199
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:43,120
The 8th Test of Courage Competition Goal

200
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:43,930
Huh?

201
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:45,490
Welcome back!

202
00:10:45,490 --> 00:10:47,750
Mei-chan!

203
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,280
I was so scared!

204
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,080
There, there. You did great.

205
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:53,380
Jiro-chan, any developments?

206
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:56,510
Shiori was constantly terrified, so it wasn't really the time.

207
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:58,880
I figured that might happen.

208
00:10:59,290 --> 00:11:02,310
Still, Akari's taking a super long time, isn't she?

209
00:11:02,310 --> 00:11:03,890
Yeah, she is.

210
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:06,140
Akari's not back yet?

211
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:09,290
Considering Tenjin's with her, she's taking way too long.

212
00:11:09,290 --> 00:11:10,000
I'll try calli—

213
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,840
Leave it! Just leave it!

214
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:14,650
What if they're in the middle of... enjoying themselves?

215
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,720
That's right. Out in the dark with no one around, just the two of them...

216
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,550
They have no choice but to do things!

217
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:23,440
I hate seeing you talking with those other girls all the time.

218
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:23,440
They wouldn't do that! They wouldn't...

219
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:27,660
What's her deal? After she said all that to me...

220
00:11:28,010 --> 00:11:30,400
And why am I irritated?

221
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,540
It's not like it matters, right?

222
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:36,650
What? It's raining!

223
00:11:36,650 --> 00:11:38,540
Ugh, seriously?

224
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,400
Oh, it's Mikkun.

225
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,950
Hello?

226
00:11:41,950 --> 00:11:43,050
What?

227
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:46,520
Okay, got it. So you're turning back, then?

228
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,860
Did something happen?

229
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:52,000
Watanabe-san dropped her phone, and while they were looking for it, they got separated.

230
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:52,690
What?

231
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,700
Are they gonna be okay?

232
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,650
Akari...

233
00:11:57,200 --> 00:12:00,240
This area is privately owned, so they're in no danger.

234
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,200
You guys can head back to your rooms.

235
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,640
Yuck! It's really raining hard!

236
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:07,010
Take care of Akari for us, boss!

237
00:12:07,010 --> 00:12:08,450
Leave it to me!

238
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:12,960
Jiro-kun, we'll get soaked.

239
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,330
Let's go back.

240
00:12:18,060 --> 00:12:19,760
Sorry, Shiori.

241
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,730
I'm going to go look for Akari.

242
00:12:21,730 --> 00:12:22,970
Jiro-kun!

243
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:28,520
What am I gonna do?

244
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:31,280
I can't find my phone, and now it's raining.

245
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,020
This seriously sucks!

246
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:36,000
Should I head back to the cottage?

247
00:12:38,180 --> 00:12:42,740
I just let Minami-kun lead me around, so I have no idea which way to go!

248
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:50,740
Akari! Akari!

249
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:54,280
The route from the station to the resort, too...

250
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:56,750
I had Jiro look all that up for me.

251
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:59,050
All I do is rely on other people.

252
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:00,240
I'm so sorry.

253
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,260
I'm sorry.

254
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,010
Jiro?!

255
00:13:10,050 --> 00:13:12,160
Minami-kun?

256
00:13:16,690 --> 00:13:18,550
This is Akari's.

257
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:21,880
Where are you, Akari?

258
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:26,690
I'm so glad you're safe.

259
00:13:26,690 --> 00:13:27,810
Minami-kun...

260
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:30,410
I'm sorry we got separated. Are you okay?

261
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:33,780
There's an azumaya gazebo over that way. Let's move there for now.

262
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:40,670
Yes. We'll head back once the rain lets up a little.

263
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:43,730
I'm very sorry. Thank you.

264
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:46,800
Are you feeling better?

265
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:51,360
Minami-kun, I'm seriously so sorry for causing you so much trouble!

266
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,310
I just went off on my own and...

267
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:58,010
No, it's okay. I failed to notice that you were gone, too.

268
00:13:58,010 --> 00:14:00,440
Just sit down and rest for now.

269
00:14:01,230 --> 00:14:02,090
Okay.

270
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,190
Oh, and...

271
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,200
Sorry I wasn't Jiro.

272
00:14:09,610 --> 00:14:10,450
Huh?!

273
00:14:13,570 --> 00:14:14,700
Your face!

274
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:17,480
I-It's not like that! That was just...

275
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:20,680
Please listen! Stop laughing, Minami-kun!

276
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:24,710
Sorry! It was just way more of a reaction than I expected.

277
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,470
I see. So it's Yakuin, huh?

278
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:29,940
Jiro has nothing to do with this!

279
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:32,880
Your face is way too red. You're not convincing at all.

280
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,600
No, just listen!

281
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,260
The person I love is...

282
00:14:36,260 --> 00:14:38,150
But it does make me feel a little sad.

283
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:38,740
Huh?

284
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:42,540
Crap. There's just so much rain!

285
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:43,730
Jiro-kun!

286
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:48,180
Jeez, Jiro-kun! I've been looking for you!

287
00:14:48,180 --> 00:14:49,110
Shiori...

288
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:52,620
Listen! They found Akari-chan!

289
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:54,100
What? For real?

290
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:56,240
Minami-kun found her.

291
00:14:57,850 --> 00:15:00,350
They're taking shelter from the rain right now.

292
00:15:00,350 --> 00:15:02,540
They'll head back once it lets up.

293
00:15:02,540 --> 00:15:04,630
Isn't that great? It's such a relief!

294
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:05,890
Yeah.

295
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:07,790
It's great.

296
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,930
You came all the way out here just to let me know?

297
00:15:15,930 --> 00:15:17,720
Well, you weren't reading your messages.

298
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,390
I was worried.

299
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:20,870
Sorry.

300
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,430
It's okay.

301
00:15:22,430 --> 00:15:25,280
I know that's just how hard you were looking for her.

302
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:28,530
You were truly worried about Akari-chan.

303
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:32,220
I was freaking out all on my own and getting nowhere.

304
00:15:32,950 --> 00:15:34,840
If Tenjin was going to find her anyway,

305
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:37,330
I should've just stayed and waited where I was.

306
00:15:37,330 --> 00:15:38,540
I'm such a loser.

307
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:40,540
You are not a loser!

308
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:42,330
You're very kind...

309
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:47,050
And since the practical started, you've become really cool.

310
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:53,000
Akari-chan knows a Jiro-kun that I don't know.

311
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,300
I envy her just a little bit.

312
00:15:55,660 --> 00:15:57,440
What are you talking about?

313
00:15:57,440 --> 00:16:00,280
The "me" you've seen all this time is the same "me" I am now.

314
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:04,120
But I've never seen the husband side of you.

315
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:06,740
I keep thinking you must be different like that.

316
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,050
You think so?

317
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:11,320
I don't think anything really changes just because you're married.

318
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:17,020
And it's not like Akari and I are actually in love with each other.

319
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,500
Jiro-kun...

320
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,830
Even that expression you're making right now is one I don't know.

321
00:16:25,180 --> 00:16:28,080
And anyway, what about you? With Tenjin, I mean.

322
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:28,650
Huh?

323
00:16:28,650 --> 00:16:30,080
You know, um...

324
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:34,590
That thing we did before... Practicing. What happened after that?

325
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:38,300
Huh? Really? You and Tenjin...

326
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:41,220
N-No! Nothing happened!

327
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:43,760
But you seem really shaken right now.

328
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:47,980
It's not that! I just remembered kissing you, and...

329
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,360
Um...

330
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:55,390
I haven't done anything like that since then.

331
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:56,480
Oh.

332
00:16:58,410 --> 00:17:02,000
My first was you...

333
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:04,750
but was it different for you?

334
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:07,000
Um... Well, I mean...

335
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:11,240
Of course! Sorry for asking such a weird question!

336
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,080
And for getting so flustered all on my own.

337
00:17:13,080 --> 00:17:13,940
Shiori?

338
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:15,630
The rain's let up now, so...

339
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:19,390
You'll get soaked.

340
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:25,880
You've been beside me all this time, and now I feel so lonely!

341
00:17:27,830 --> 00:17:32,780
Once we grow up, being childhood friends won't be enough to keep me by your side.

342
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:37,280
I'm so sorry. I just... Akari-chan is...

343
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:42,160
If Akari-chan isn't special to you,

344
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:43,570
then will you show me...

345
00:17:44,650 --> 00:17:46,660
a part of you that

346
00:17:47,690 --> 00:17:49,380
Akari-chan doesn't know?

347
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:59,300
Minami-kun, um... What did you mean when you said you felt sad?

348
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:01,600
Hmm... It's like...

349
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:06,140
how an older brother feels getting introduced to his little sister's boyfriend?

350
00:18:06,140 --> 00:18:07,190
Little sister?

351
00:18:07,990 --> 00:18:09,060
Yeah.

352
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:13,760
Oh. I get it.

353
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,660
He's turning me down right now.

354
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,430
But I have to give it my very best.

355
00:18:19,430 --> 00:18:22,200
Because I made a promise with Jiro

356
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:25,080
that we'd get to A-rank and change partners!

357
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,930
Minami-kun, if...

358
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:34,010
If I became your wife and we spent time together in the marriage practical,

359
00:18:34,010 --> 00:18:38,340
then would that feeling of me being your little sister...

360
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:40,340
Huh?

361
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:44,350
Why am I trying so hard again?

362
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:48,680
Watanabe, I'm sorry. The truth is, I noticed a long time ago

363
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,730
that you were looking at me that way.

364
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:51,520
Huh?

365
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:53,040
What?!

366
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,980
I mean, it'd be hard not to notice.

367
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,940
It really made me happy that you felt that way,

368
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,740
but I'm in love with someone else.

369
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,590
It's Sakurazaka-san, isn't it?

370
00:19:06,590 --> 00:19:07,250
Huh? Huh?

371
00:19:10,450 --> 00:19:12,440
Hang on! You've got this way wrong!

372
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,900
Huh? What? You... Huh?

373
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:17,050
So that's what you thought, huh?

374
00:19:17,050 --> 00:19:19,010
Please stop laughing!

375
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:22,920
Sorry. There's nothing between me and Shiori.

376
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,070
What? You're kidding.

377
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:26,200
Who, then? Someone in your class?

378
00:19:27,860 --> 00:19:29,680
It's someone you don't know.

379
00:19:32,410 --> 00:19:33,990
It's an unrequited love.

380
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:36,630
And it'll probably stay that way forever.

381
00:19:39,190 --> 00:19:42,770
A love with no future is just pointless.

382
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,940
I know how much that hurts,

383
00:19:46,410 --> 00:19:49,240
so when I think about how I've made you go through the same thing,

384
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,410
I just feel so bad.

385
00:19:52,530 --> 00:19:55,560
That's why I was relieved when I heard Yakuin's name.

386
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:56,460
I'm happy for you.

387
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,260
Even if...

388
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:02,180
Even if Jiro's in love with someone else, too?

389
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:04,370
Yakuin's dating someone?

390
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:06,720
No, he isn't, but...

391
00:20:07,630 --> 00:20:09,970
Then it's all up to how hard you try, isn't it?

392
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:13,310
There's still a chance that Yakuin will choose you, right?

393
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:16,930
B-But what if I tell him and it makes things weird between us?

394
00:20:17,580 --> 00:20:20,070
You used to be more optimistic about stuff than that.

395
00:20:20,650 --> 00:20:22,360
Are things weird between us now?

396
00:20:23,820 --> 00:20:24,930
No.

397
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:29,820
I hope your love is something you can enjoy this time.

398
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,580
It's like I'm entrusting my hopes to you...

399
00:20:33,370 --> 00:20:35,510
Because it's something I wasn't able to do.

400
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:39,060
Sorry to do this after you were kind enough to fall in love with me.

401
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:42,540
That's wrong!

402
00:20:43,090 --> 00:20:46,220
Because I've had so much fun all this time!

403
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:49,380
Every time we talked, my heart raced so fast.

404
00:20:49,380 --> 00:20:51,600
When our eyes met, I'd be walking on clouds.

405
00:20:51,910 --> 00:20:54,600
So please don't say things like that.

406
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:58,110
I didn't fall in love with you to make you apologize to me.

407
00:20:58,110 --> 00:21:01,150
Thank you, Minami-kun. I mean it.

408
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:03,400
I really loved you!

409
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,610
I'm the one who should thank you.

410
00:21:07,370 --> 00:21:08,910
Your feelings have reached me.

411
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:11,430
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

412
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:15,860
I want to give love a try

413
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:14,530
I'm glad I fell in love.

414
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:18,910
I'm truly glad I fell in love with this guy. In this night when everything begins to overflow

415
00:21:18,770 --> 00:21:21,040
I match my stride to yours

416
00:21:20,220 --> 00:21:21,130
Okay!

417
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:26,880
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

418
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:22,500
I'll give it my best!

419
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:26,260
I'll try my hardest with Jiro so that I won't have any regrets!

420
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:29,580
Being upbeat is much more like you.

421
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:31,450
The answers always slip away

422
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,990
I gotta hurry up and move forward, too.

423
00:21:31,450 --> 00:21:34,870
All I want is to do it over again You'll be able to find someone right away.

424
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:36,270
Thanks. I'll do my best.

425
00:21:34,870 --> 00:21:40,270
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

426
00:21:40,270 --> 00:21:44,570
I want to know where my heart is hiding

427
00:21:44,570 --> 00:21:49,350
One day this will end

428
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:50,880
It's Sakurazaka-san, isn't it?

429
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:52,150
I know that

430
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:54,140
I never imagined she'd think that. And I know the signs of discord

431
00:21:53,860 --> 00:21:55,910
Turn them inside out

432
00:21:54,670 --> 00:21:57,840
And Shiori seems like she has someone she's in love with, too.

433
00:21:55,910 --> 00:21:57,510
Don't let them pile up

434
00:21:57,510 --> 00:22:01,720
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

435
00:21:57,840 --> 00:22:00,540
I hope it hasn't kicked off any weird rumors.

436
00:22:01,430 --> 00:22:03,170
But in any case...

437
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:05,760
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

438
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:07,160
I hope it works out for both of them.

439
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:10,190
I want to give love a try

440
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:12,210
Everything begins to overflow

441
00:22:12,210 --> 00:22:15,400
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

442
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:21,670
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

443
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:39,370
It's my fault

444
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:40,540
It gets stuck in my throat

445
00:22:40,540 --> 00:22:42,830
That stagnant, hesitant air

446
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:43,890
And turns into a thorn

447
00:22:43,890 --> 00:22:46,310
When that happens, no matter how much time passes,

448
00:22:46,310 --> 00:22:48,780
I'll never be able to forget it

449
00:22:48,780 --> 00:22:50,990
It's your fault

450
00:22:50,990 --> 00:22:56,070
That my fragile heart is so stirred into action

451
00:22:56,070 --> 00:23:00,160
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

452
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:04,610
I want to give love a try

453
00:23:04,610 --> 00:23:07,520
In this night where everything begins to overflow

454
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:09,800
I match my stride to yours

455
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:14,490
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

456
00:23:14,490 --> 00:23:19,960
No matter what I sing, no matter what I eat

457
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:24,740
The only one I want to tell about it is you

458
00:23:24,740 --> 00:23:27,860
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

459
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:36,120
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

460
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:44,540
(Oh why)

461
00:23:46,990 --> 00:23:49,040
(Oh why)

462
00:23:50,340 --> 00:23:52,680
How long are they gonna stay like that?

463
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:54,240
They should just hook up already.

464
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,960
You don't understand a thing!

465
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:56,490
What?

466
00:23:56,490 --> 00:23:58,830
You don't understand a thing!

467
00:23:58,830 --> 00:23:59,760
Natsumi!

468
00:23:59,760 --> 00:24:01,500
This is a declaration of war!

469
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:04,000
Stop, Natsumi! Come back to your senses!

470
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,500
Get dizzy from staying in the bath too long, the lot of you.

471
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:09,990
Next Time Done, Being Less Than Love.

472
00:24:07,540 --> 00:24:09,410
Next time, "Done, Being Less Than Love."

